for five seconds.

1127
01:14:41,189 --> 01:14:43,180
Five seconds.

1128
01:14:46,761 --> 01:14:50,492
[Both]
One, two, three...

1129
01:14:50,565 --> 01:14:52,863
four, five.

1130
01:14:56,604 --> 01:14:58,936
You gotta hold her head still
so she won't move.

1131
01:15:05,546 --> 01:15:08,947
Dear God, guide my hand.

1132
01:15:26,434 --> 01:15:28,304
[Mouths Words]

1133
01:15:41,150 --> 01:15:44,313
Looks like she'll be fine.

1134
01:15:44,387 --> 01:15:47,083
Belinda, what you did-

1135
01:15:47,156 --> 01:15:51,559
It could have gone the other way.
I could have lost her, Drew.

1136
01:15:51,627 --> 01:15:53,652
But you didn't.

1137
01:15:53,729 --> 01:15:57,722
You were smart enough to figure out what to do
and brave enough to do it.

1138
01:15:59,535 --> 01:16:02,436
I was terrified the whole time.

1139
01:16:02,505 --> 01:16:04,939
- It didn't stop you.
- <i>[Door Opens]</i>

1140
01:16:06,809 --> 01:16:11,439
<i>Oh, Belinda, I have been</i>
<i>looking all over for you.</i>

1141
01:16:15,718 --> 01:16:19,017
What's happened? What is it?

1142
01:16:19,088 --> 01:16:21,784
Belinda saved my daughter's life.

1143
01:16:26,696 --> 01:16:29,824
How are you?
Open up for me.

1144
01:16:29,899 --> 01:16:34,734
Well, I bet that throat is really sore, huh?

1145
01:16:34,804 --> 01:16:38,467
Good excuse for your mama
to churn some fresh buttermilk for ya.

1146
01:16:38,541 --> 01:16:41,704
- I sure will.
- [Chuckles]

1147
01:16:52,822 --> 01:16:56,258
<i>You know,</i>
<i>you saved her life.</i>

1148
01:16:56,325 --> 01:16:58,293
But I didn't save Jonas's.

1149
01:16:58,361 --> 01:17:01,296
Yes, um, about that.

1150
01:17:02,598 --> 01:17:04,725
[Sighs]

1151
01:17:04,800 --> 01:17:08,395
I owe you a very big apology.

1152
01:17:08,471 --> 01:17:11,963
Jonas's death wasn't your fault.

1153
01:17:12,041 --> 01:17:14,100
But I couldn't hold him still.

1154
01:17:14,177 --> 01:17:16,270
But that's not why he died.

1155
01:17:16,345 --> 01:17:20,213
<i>Jonas was dying</i>
<i>when he came to us.</i>

1156
01:17:20,283 --> 01:17:23,446
We were trying to save him,
but unfortunately...

1157
01:17:23,519 --> 01:17:26,920
the surgery was
just too much for him.

1158
01:17:26,989 --> 01:17:30,823
I told you how difficult
it is losing a patient.

1159
01:17:30,893 --> 01:17:35,956
<i>I've been practicing</i>
<i>for 40 years, give or take...</i>

1160
01:17:36,032 --> 01:17:38,023
and it never gets any easier.

1161
01:17:38,100 --> 01:17:40,432
When it hurts this much...

1162
01:17:40,503 --> 01:17:43,961
it just means that...

1163
01:17:44,040 --> 01:17:46,531
you care that much more
about your patients.

1164
01:17:46,609 --> 01:17:50,101
Um, I don't think
I'm cut out to be a doctor.

1165
01:17:50,179 --> 01:17:52,647
Oh, yes, you are, young lady.

1166
01:17:52,715 --> 01:17:57,652
<i>You go back to Boston</i>
<i>with Mrs. Stafford-Smith.</i>

1167
01:17:57,720 --> 01:18:02,453
But you just make darn sure that
you come back here when you're a doctor.

1168
01:18:03,893 --> 01:18:05,827
Doc-

1169
01:18:05,895 --> 01:18:08,625
Well, now...

1170
01:18:08,698 --> 01:18:11,963
don't start crying or I'll-

1171
01:18:12,034 --> 01:18:14,969
I'll think I made
a mistake after all.

1172
01:18:23,446 --> 01:18:25,437
Whoa.

1173
01:18:33,289 --> 01:18:35,985
That's for having more faith in me
than I had in myself.

1174
01:18:57,747 --> 01:19:00,079
Come on. Hup.

1175
01:19:03,619 --> 01:19:06,816
Are you sure you don't want us
to see you off at the stagecoach?

1176
01:19:06,889 --> 01:19:10,791
I'd rather we say good-bye here.

1177
01:19:10,860 --> 01:19:14,296
You know, by train Boston
isn't as far as it once seemed.

1178
01:19:14,363 --> 01:19:16,297
Mm-hmm.

1179
01:19:16,365 --> 01:19:19,630
- Are you all right, Belinda?
- Yes, Mama, I'm fine.

1180
01:19:19,702 --> 01:19:22,535
No second thoughts about leaving
with Mrs. Stafford-Smith?

1181
01:19:22,605 --> 01:19:27,269
No, not anymore.
I feel at peace with my decision.

1182
01:19:27,343 --> 01:19:29,573
So your second thoughts
are about Drew?

1183
01:19:30,680 --> 01:19:34,616
I love him, Mama.
I really do.

1184
01:19:34,684 --> 01:19:36,743
But it could never work.

1185
01:19:36,819 --> 01:19:39,549
Sometimes one dream
is all you can have.

1186
01:19:49,532 --> 01:19:52,126
- Whoa. Whoa.
- [Neighs]

1187
01:19:52,201 --> 01:19:54,135
- Morning.
- Mornin'.

1188
01:19:58,941 --> 01:20:02,968
I just wanted to say good-bye, Clark,
and thank you for everything.

1189
01:20:03,045 --> 01:20:07,004
- You headed home?
- Charles and Sadie are moving onto the farm.

1190
01:20:07,083 --> 01:20:10,780
I'm headed... back
to New York tomorrow.

1191
01:20:10,853 --> 01:20:13,788
<i>I, uh, imagine Belinda left.</i>

1192
01:20:13,856 --> 01:20:17,189
We said our good-byes
with Missie this mornin'.

1193
01:20:17,259 --> 01:20:20,251
She's probably getting
on the stage right about now.

1194
01:20:20,329 --> 01:20:25,096
You asked me once
when I knew I loved Marty.

1195
01:20:25,167 --> 01:20:27,931
- But you never asked me what I did about it.
- What was that?

1196
01:20:28,003 --> 01:20:32,440
She left on a wagon train.
She was going back home.

1197
01:20:34,510 --> 01:20:36,944
I went after her.

1198
01:20:37,012 --> 01:20:40,209
If you love someone, if you truly love them,
you don't let them go.

1199
01:20:43,552 --> 01:20:47,716
- I've learned a lot from you.
- Then what are you doing still standing here?

1200
01:20:49,225 --> 01:20:51,989
Don't you have a stage to catch?

1201
01:21:01,203 --> 01:21:05,162
Last call, Denver stage!
All aboard, folks!

1202
01:21:05,241 --> 01:21:08,472
- <i>Last call, Denver stage!</i>
- Come on.

1203
01:21:08,544 --> 01:21:10,478
Whoa. Belinda!

1204
01:21:10,546 --> 01:21:12,343
Oh, my goodness.

1205
01:21:13,816 --> 01:21:16,683
Don't go!

1206
01:21:19,121 --> 01:21:22,386
I'll practice in Boston while you're in school.
Then we'll come back here.

1207
01:21:22,458 --> 01:21:24,824
You'd be happy practicing law
in Anderson Corner?

1208
01:21:24,894 --> 01:21:29,797
Anderson Corner is the place
I learned to love the law, and it has you.

1209
01:21:29,865 --> 01:21:31,924
I don't think I could be
truly happy anywhere else.

1210
01:21:32,001 --> 01:21:35,698
- This isn't your world, Drew.
- You're my world.

1211
01:21:38,707 --> 01:21:41,608
I love you, Belinda.
Marry me.

1212
01:21:46,749 --> 01:21:51,482
Oh, there's a train back to Boston most every day.
You'll catch one next week.

1213
01:21:51,554 --> 01:21:54,079
Windsor will meet you at the depot.
Won't you, Windsor?

1214
01:21:57,760 --> 01:22:01,355
I'd love to marry you, Drew.

1215
01:22:28,691 --> 01:22:30,682
[Kisses Cheek]

1216
01:22:37,500 --> 01:22:41,129
Do you, Andrew, take Belinda
to be your lawfully wedded wife...

1217
01:22:41,203 --> 01:22:44,661
<i>to have and to hold,</i>
<i>for richer and for poorer...</i>

1218
01:22:44,740 --> 01:22:49,439
<i>in sickness and in health, forsaking</i>
<i>all others, till death do you part?</i>

1219
01:22:49,512 --> 01:22:52,310
- I do.
- <i>And do you, Belinda, take Andrew...</i>

1220
01:22:52,381 --> 01:22:54,110
<i>to be your lawfully</i>
<i>wedded husband...</i>

1221
01:22:54,183 --> 01:22:57,516
<i>to have and to hold,</i>
<i>for richer and for poorer...</i>

1222
01:22:57,586 --> 01:23:00,316
<i>in sickness and in health,</i>
<i>forsaking all others...</i>

1223
01:23:00,389 --> 01:23:03,119
- <i>till death do you part?</i>
- I do.

1224
01:23:18,340 --> 01:23:21,104
I now pronounce you man and wife.

1225
01:23:21,176 --> 01:23:23,167
<i>[Applause]</i>

1226
01:23:39,328 --> 01:23:41,455
[Man]
You do look happy.

1227
01:23:41,530 --> 01:23:44,522
- [Guests Chattering]
- [Laughs]

1228
01:24:11,594 --> 01:24:13,391
[Kisses Cheek]

1229
01:24:13,462 --> 01:24:15,930
Bye.

1230
01:24:15,998 --> 01:24:17,761
Mmm. Be safe.

1231
01:24:17,833 --> 01:24:20,597
You know I will.
You know I will.

1232
01:24:20,669 --> 01:24:22,603
Take care, son.

1233
01:24:22,671 --> 01:24:25,572
- Thank you so much.
- Bless you.

1234
01:24:28,277 --> 01:24:30,802
[Both Laugh]

1235
01:24:30,879 --> 01:24:33,507
- Bye, Grandpa.
- Take care, honey.

1236
01:24:33,582 --> 01:24:36,050
[Both Laugh]

1237
01:24:36,118 --> 01:24:37,779
Come here, Jacob.

1238
01:24:39,455 --> 01:24:42,049
Be good.

1239
01:24:42,124 --> 01:24:44,684
Marty.

1240
01:24:44,760 --> 01:24:47,024
Take care.

1241
01:24:48,664 --> 01:24:51,724
- Thank you.
- Absolutely.

1242
01:24:51,800 --> 01:24:55,292
- Take care of my girl.
- Will do.

1243
01:25:01,210 --> 01:25:04,043
You ready?

1244
01:25:04,113 --> 01:25:06,707
[Laughs]

1245
01:25:06,782 --> 01:25:08,545
Bye.

1246
01:25:09,818 --> 01:25:13,049
[Drew Clicking Tongue]
Giddap!

1247
01:25:13,122 --> 01:25:15,090
Bye!

1248
01:25:17,192 --> 01:25:19,820
- Love you!
- [All] Bye!

1249
01:25:27,169 --> 01:25:29,501
[Belinda]
Love you!

1250
